For the Monkey, humans are just another animal species.
You need to sleep, eat and create a new generation. This could work in prehistoric times.
But if you haven't noticed, we don't live in prehistoric times.
We live in an advanced civilization and the Monkey does not know what it is.
That's why we have another person in our brain, the Rational Decision Maker who gives us the ability to do things that no other animal can do.
We can project ourselves into the future.
We can get an overview of the situation.
We can make long-term plans.
And he wants to take all that into account.
And he wants us to do just what makes sense, here and now.
Sometimes it makes sense to do things that are easy and fun, like when you're having dinner or going to bed or enjoying some well-deserved free time.
There is overlap. Sometimes they agree.
But on other occasions, it makes much more sense to do things that are more difficult and less enjoyable, for the sake of the bigger picture.
A conflict is then created.
